{"TopicId":157313,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Modpacks, should they be banned?","CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-04T14:22:03Z","PageNum":8,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-07T22:58:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978994\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488923332\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nascarlaser1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, nascarlaser1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbefore I post my opinion, what is a modpack?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGenerally speaking:\u00A0A\u00A0compilation of mods redistributed as one large package, usually with few or no\u00A0new modifications of their own.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nascarlaser1","CreatedById":166190,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-07T22:59:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222979057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022157313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488927523\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGenerally speaking:\u00A0A\u00A0compilation of mods redistributed as one large package, usually with few or no\u00A0new modifications of their own.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh. In that case I don\u0027t have an opinion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-08T10:03:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fixed addon rules are now live, modpacks are not banned but packers (and modders including dependencies) must provide information on every addon they include.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese rule changes are not retroactive so existing mods are not affected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154851-add-on-posting-rules-march-8-2017/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe poll is now closed, if it does become necessary to ban modpacks as described in the addon rules then that can be done at a later date.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThread is now closed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}